        <name>_module_contract</name>
        <qualifiedname>dedoc.api.schema._module_contract</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Aggregate and re-export all API schema classes for external consumers, providing a single import point for the dedoc API schema layer. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Public API schema surface — Pydantic models for document representation. \par \b Input\/ \:  None (re-exports from sibling modules). \par \b Output\/ \:  Flat namespace of all schema classes via <bold>all</bold>. \par \b Links\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>all</bold> always contains all public schema class names.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>All names in <bold>all</bold> resolve to actual classes via relative imports. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why centralize exports? A: Provides a stable public API contract. External consumers import from <computeroutput><ref refid="namespacededoc_1_1api_1_1schema" kindref="compound">dedoc.api.schema</ref></computeroutput> without knowing internal module layout. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Initial creation with semantic markup] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>EXPORT [Aggregates schema classes for public API] =&gt; <bold>all</bold> \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[<bold>all</bold>]: ExternalConsumer =&gt; ImportSchemaNamespace =&gt; DiscoverAvailableSchemaClasses </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
